      description:
        "Here at Ocado Logistics, it’s our mission to provide an outstanding customer experience for our partners, developing ground-breaking technology, opening multiple sites at an accelerating rate, and engaging in exciting new business partnerships around the world - changing the way the world shops, for good.\r\nWe are the beating heart of our UK business, comprising a network of cutting-edge warehouses and offices across the country that optimise operations through our proprietary technology. We ensure an exceptional shopping experience while delivering career opportunities that offer variety and progression.\r\nAbout the role\r\nWe wouldn’t be able to positively impact the way the world shops without our passionate team members - who keep our business running, our vans delivering, our customers' products picked and packed, and our proprietary technology operating at optimum levels.\r\nWe now have an opportunity for an Area Coordinator to join the team at Bicester CFC. In this role, you will play a key part in ensuring smooth operational workflow, compliance, and excellent service delivery. If you thrive in a fast-paced environment, have strong communication skills, and are passionate about safety and efficiency, this could be the role for you!\r\nWe operate a rotating shift pattern of 4 days on, 4 days off, from 12.00pm to 12.00am (45 hours weekly average)\r\nKey Responsibilities\r\n- Safety First: Maintain high health & safety standards, ensuring compliance with SSOWs and risk assessments while actively identifying and removing hazards.\r\n- People & Team Engagement: Foster an inclusive and supportive team culture, ensure clear communication, onboard new team members, and contribute to key workforce KPIs (labour turnover, absence, and engagement).\r\n- Operational Efficiency: Capture and manage headcounts, ensuring fair deployment, and coordinate tasks to meet productivity and performance targets.\r\n- Quality & Compliance: Ensure all processes adhere to HACCP and food safety standards, working closely with food technology teams on any issues.\r\n- Continuous Improvement: Identify and resolve operational challenges, escalate issues where needed, and drive best practices for efficiency gains.\r\nAbout you\r\n- Strong communication skills (verbal and written).\r\n- Proficient numerical skills with the ability to analyse and interpret data.\r\n- A KPI-driven mindset with the ability to set and achieve performance goals.\r\n- Adaptability in a fast-moving operational environment.\r\n- A strong commitment to safety and high working standards.\r\n- Basic IT proficiency (Excel, Google, Microsoft Office).\r\nPreferred experience\r\n- Knowledge of food safety and compliance standards.\r\n- Experience in a 24/7 logistics or warehouse operation.\r\n- Familiarity with Warehouse Management Systems.\r\n- Previous people management or leadership experience.\r\n- Experience using Mechanical Handling Equipment (MHE).\r\nAdditional Requirements\r\n- Ability to stand/walk for extended periods.\r\n- Lift objects up to 30kg periodically.\r\n- Work in varying temperatures (30°C to -30°C).\r\n- Flexibility to work shifts, including weekends, in a 24/7 operation.\r\nWhat you can expect in return\r\nAt Ocado, we believe in a workplace where everyone feels valued and supported. You’ll find a safe and collaborative atmosphere, an award-winning recognition programme, and a benefits package designed to support your well-being and career growth, including:\r\nPension Plan: Up to 7% employer contribution matching.\r\nWellbeing Support: Employee Assistance Programme and well-being apps.\r\nGenerous Leave: 270 hrs to 288 hrs ( after 5 years in service) + the option to buy more.\r\nFamily-Friendly Policies: Carer's Leave, Maternity, Adoption, Shared Parental Leave, and\r\nPaternity leave.\r\nShare Schemes: Participate in our success through share plans.\r\nLifestyle Benefits: Cycle to Work scheme, car salary sacrifice, and more.\r\nShopping Perks: 15% discount on Ocado.com and savings at major retailers, restaurants, and entertainment venues.\r\nOcado Group is an equal opportunities employer and is committed to ensuring all potential employees are treated fairly and equally, regardless of sex, sexual\r\norientation, marital status, race, nationality, ethnic or national origin, religion or belief, age, disability, or union membership status.\r\nJoin Ocado Logistics today and become part of a culture that values and supports your well-being at every stage of your career.\r\n",
