      description:
        "Technical Assistant\r\nOcado Logistics, Dordon\r\nPermanent- Competitive Salary on offer\r\n\r\nOcado Logistics, part of the Ocado Group, is a global leader in technology-driven online grocery and e-commerce fulfilment, managing the end-to-end transport and logistics that power our operations.\r\n\r\nOur state-of-the-art Customer Fulfilment Centres (CFCs) are fast-paced, highly automated environments that rely on cutting-edge technology to deliver excellence at scale.\r\n\r\nThe Dordon CFC is a £200 million flagship facility – the largest, most advanced, and most productive grocery fulfilment centre of its kind anywhere in the world.\r\n\r\nTo keep our world-class systems running at their best, we’re looking for a Technical Assistant (Shift) to join our Engineering Operations team – helping maintain equipment, support maintenance activities, and ensure technical areas remain safe, clean, and efficient.\r\n\r\nThe Role\r\nAs a Technical Assistant, you’ll play a key part in ensuring our engineering operations run seamlessly.\r\nThe role is shift based to support the 24/7 operation of the CFC. You will work the Panama shift pattern to support continuous operations, benefiting from a competitive salary and benefits.\r\n\r\nYou’ll be responsible for:\r\n- Supporting maintenance activities across the site.\r\n- Keeping technical areas safe, clean, and organised to a high standard.\r\n- Resolving minor faults within your training and escalating issues where needed.\r\n- Assisting the engineering team on planned and reactive maintenance tasks.\r\n- Ensuring equipment is cared for, secure, and used safely.\r\n- Completing paperwork accurately and on time\r\n\r\nCollaboration & Communication\r\nStrong communication is key – you’ll escalate issues promptly and share knowledge with your team to help everyone succeed. You’ll work closely with:\r\n\r\n- Engineering Operations Management\r\n- CFC Operations\r\n- Buildings Technology\r\n- Project Engineering\r\n- Site Services\r\n-\r\n We’re looking for someone who is:\r\n\r\n- Organised, with the ability to prioritise tasks effectively.\r\n- A good problem-solver with a practical approach.\r\n- A clear communicator, able to produce simple reports when needed.\r\n- Flexible in working patterns to meet business needs.\r\n- Self-motivated, consistent, and able to work at pace.\r\n- A real team player who shares knowledge and supports colleagues.\r\n** Previous experience in an engineering service support role within an automated production environment would be highly advantageous **\r\n\r\n\r\nWhat you can expect to receive in return -\r\nAt Ocado we believe in a workplace where everyone feels valued and supported, so you’ll find a safe and collaborative atmosphere that is as fresh as our produce as well as an award winning recognition programme and benefits package that includes a healthy work-life balance, extensive healthcare coverage, competitive salaries, and exclusive employee discounts.\r\n\r\nClear progression paths available at all levels within our team. We've seen many individuals successfully advance from technical assistant to technician, then to engineer, and ultimately into management roles.\r\n\r\nJoin Ocado Logistics today and become a part of a culture that wholeheartedly values and supports your well-being throughout every stage of your career.\r\n\r\nImportant Note: You must have the Right to Work in the UK to be considered for this role. We are unable to provide sponsorship for this role.\r\n\r\n",
