        '12 Month Fixed Term Contract (FTC) Opportunities Available\r\nPlease note: This position is not eligible for visa sponsorship. Candidates must already have the right to work in the UK for the duration of the contract.\r\n\r\nDemand Planner\r\nAt Ocado Logistics, we’re changing the way the world shops. Our cutting-edge technology and customer-first approach keep us at the forefront of retail innovation. Join us to make a real impact on the future of supply management.\r\n\r\nAbout the Role:\r\nThis hybrid role requires in-office presence twice a week at our Head Office in Hatfield.\r\nAs a Demand Planner, you’ll drive the success of our product range by managing forecasts, supplier performance, and key KPIs. You’ll work closely with trading teams and suppliers to keep our supply chain running smoothly.\r\n\r\nThis position is a 12 month Fixed Term Contract (FTC)\r\n\r\nWhat You’ll Be Doing:\r\n- Manage demand and forecast planning across ~2,500 products\r\n- Use data to achieve KPIs for availability, waste, and fulfilment\r\n- Build strong supplier relationships and conduct performance reviews\r\n- Optimise delivery schedules and buying processes\r\n- Support promotional, seasonal, and new product planning\r\n- Analyse trends and recommend improvements\r\n- Act as a point of contact for supply chain queries\r\n- Collaborate on process development and system improvements\r\n\r\nAbout You:\r\n- Experience in FMCG, supply chain, merchandising, or logistics\r\n- Skilled in demand forecasting and data analysis\r\n- Confident communicator and relationship builder\r\n- Strong Excel and IT skills\r\n- Organised, adaptable, and proactive in fast-paced environments\r\n- Able to make decisions independently\r\n- Willing to work occasional weekends on a rota\r\n\r\nPreferred:\r\n- Commercial acumen and supplier management experience\r\n- Background in e-commerce or large-scale retail supply chains\r\n\r\nThe Interview Process:\r\nOur process has two stages. After an initial screening call with Richard Wandowski, our Lead Recruiter, you’ll prepare a short presentation. You’ll then meet senior team members to discuss your experience and approach.\r\n\r\nBenefits and More:\r\n- Flexible hybrid working and 30 days a year ‘work from anywhere’\r\n- 25 days holiday, rising to 27 after 5 years\r\n- Pension with up to 7% employer contributions\r\n- Private medical insurance and income protection\r\n- Employee Assistance Programme and wellbeing apps\r\n- Family-friendly policies\r\n- Share schemes and free shares\r\n- 15% discount on Ocado.com and partner retailers\r\n- Free shuttle buses and Cycle to Work Scheme\r\n\r\nOcado Group is an equal opportunities employer and ensures fair and equal treatment for all potential employees, regardless of sex, sexual orientation, marital status, race, colour, nationality, ethnic or national origin, religion or belief, age, disability, or union membership status.\r\n\r\n#LI-ST1\r\n#LI-HYBRID\r\n#LI-OL\r\n',
