      description:
        'Analyst – Supply Chain\r\nDepartment: Supply Chain – Ocado Logistics\r\nWe have an opportunity for an Analyst to join the Supply Chain team within Ocado Logistics. The role exists to provide data, reporting and analysis to support decision-making across Logistics. You’ll play a key part in improving performance, supporting projects, and enabling data-led solutions for our stakeholders.\r\nAs part of the Analytics team, you’ll work closely with colleagues across Operations, Planning, Finance, Retail and Technology – with great exposure to different areas of the business.\r\nYou will be\r\n- Providing data, reporting and analysis that helps drive decisions across Logistics.\r\n- Consolidating and working with data from multiple sources alongside Data Services and Technology.\r\n- Analysing trends, identifying root causes and supporting KPI improvement.\r\n- Contributing to cross-departmental projects and presenting your insights to stakeholders.\r\n- Delivering operational requests from the business, ensuring best-practice security management.\r\nAbout you\r\nTo be successful in this role, you’ll bring:\r\n- Experience as an Analyst, ideally in a Logistics or Supply Chain environment.\r\n- Strong data analysis and problem-solving skills.\r\n- Technical experience with SQL, VBA or other programming/scripting languages.\r\n- Familiarity with BI tools and data visualisation.\r\n- The ability to work with stakeholders at all levels, communicating insights clearly.\r\n- A proactive, can-do approach with strong organisational skills.\r\nThis role offers the chance to grow your career at Ocado Logistics, develop new skills, and work on impactful projects across the business. It’s a great opportunity to broaden your exposure, strengthen your technical expertise, and make a tangible impact on how we operate.\r\n\r\nPlease note: This position is not eligible for visa sponsorship. Candidates must already have the right to work in the UK for the duration of the contract.\r\nInterested?\r\nPlease apply via the internal careers portal. Don’t forget to speak to your line manager before submitting your application.\r\n',
